# Keep the Docker build context lean and free of secrets, PII, and regenerated artifacts.
# Dockerfiles COPY source dirs then reinstall/rebuild inside the image, so none of the excluded
# paths are needed at build time. (Only affects the LOCAL build context — inter-stage
# `COPY --from=builder` is unaffected, so the builder's freshly-built target/dist still ship.)

# Version control + CI (never needed in an image; .git is ~18MB of context)
.git
.gitignore
.github

# Dependencies + build caches — reinstalled/rebuilt inside the image
**/node_modules
**/target
**/.venv
**/.venv312
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc

# cargo-mutants output (local mutation-testing runs, gitignored but present on disk) — realtime-
# gateway's and platform-api's Dockerfiles COPY services/shared-ticket wholesale (a path
# dependency), so without this a `docker build` run while mutants.out exists on disk (a normal
# state during/after a mutation-testing session) bakes ~1.3MB of unrelated test-run logs into
# both images' build context.
**/mutants.out
**/mutants.out.old

# Runtime data / PII — must NEVER be baked into a distributable image.
# e.g. services/ml-inference/audio-storage holds real learner recordings (gitignored, but present
# on disk, so a bare `COPY services/ml-inference/ ...` would otherwise pull it into the image).
**/audio-storage
services/ml-inference/audio-storage

# Secrets and local env
.env
.env.*
secrets
**/*.pem
**/*.key

# Logs, coverage, OS/editor + agent/scratch cruft
**/*.log
coverage
.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
.claude
scratchpad
